HEADWORD: Rallis
<hw>Ral"li⟦eacute⟧s"</hw> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧l`y⟦amac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[F., p. p. pl. See <er>Rally</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <def>A French political group, also known as the
Constitutional Right from its position in the Chambers, mainly
monarchists who rallied to the support of the Republic in obedience to
the encyclical put forth by <person>Pope Leo XIII.</person> in Feb.,
1892.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ralline</ent>⟦br⟧
